comments: Merrill (CLE) rests and removes his hand from DiVincenzo's (NYK) front and the contact off-ball is marginal.
Bogdanovic's (NYK) arm briefly comes around Garland's (CLE) arm as they engage in the post and the marginal contact dissolves shortly thereafter.
Mobley (CLE) legally contests Hart's (NYK) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Hart (NYK) retracts his arm from Garland's (CLE) space and avoids making illegal contact with the offensive player at the end of the drive.
DiVincenzo (NYK) establishes himself in Mobley's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Hartenstein (NYK) brings his forearm to rest on Allen's (CLE) back as the shot is released into the air and and the pair briefly engage and disengage with one another rebounding opportunity.
Mobley (CLE) raises his right arm up and cleanly blocks Hartenstein's (NYK) shot attempt in the paint.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Merrill's (CLE) shot attempt bounces off of the rim and comes into contact with the part of the basket that is behind the backboard and out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to New York.
Garland (CLE) reaches in for the ball and makes contact with DiVincenzo's (NYK) body, which affects his SQBR while in control of the ball.
Wade (CLE) moves alongside Bogdanovic's (NYK) path and absorbs the marginal contact as the two players come together during the drive into the frontcourt.
DiVincenzo (NYK) splits his feet prior to releasing the ball to start his dribble.
Hartenstein (NYK) grasps and releases Allen's (CLE) arm as they engage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Play is stopped due to a clock malfunction. After the correction, play resumes with Cleveland retaining possession.
Hart (NYK) brings his hand toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with Garland's (CLE) arm during the drive into the paint.
DiVincenzo (NYK) is in control of the ball when the shot clock expires and possession is properly awarded to Cleveland.
